metadata.name: Proto alphabet #83
metadata.description:
For more than 4000 years, before Lineal A in Crete, proto alphabets were created. They freed man from the chains of evolution and gave a way to record the rhythm of the passage of time.

As recursion generates a grammar, recursion generates the strokes that shape the following proto alphabets, which attempt to record the passage of time.

Time is the substance I am made of. Time is a river which sweeps me along, but I am the river; it is a tiger which destroys me, but I am the tiger; it is a fire which consumes me, but I am the fire. - Jorge Luis Borges


Desde hace más de 4000 años, antes Lineal A en Creta, proto alfabetos fueron creados. Liberaron al hombre de las cadenas de la evolución y dieron una forma para registrar el ritmo del paso del tiempo.

Como la recursividad genera una gramática, la recursividad genera los trazos que dan forma a los siguientes proto alfabetos, los cuales intentan registrar el paso del tiempo.

El tiempo es la sustancia de que estoy hecho. El tiempo es un río que me arrebata, pero yo soy el río; es un tigre que me destroza, pero yo soy el tigre; es un fuego que me consume, pero yo soy el fuego. - Jorge Luis Borges


Controls (in live view):
- Press s to get a PNG file
- Press S to get a SVG file

Artwork by x0y0z0 @x0y0z0tn (2023)

metadata.name: DOOMKATS #170
metadata.description:
DOOMKATS have arrived, the favored cats of Death and the DOOMBUDS themselves. Join our feline army as we spread chaos across the world on our quest for treasure!

555 DOOMKATS will be ready to summon on Fx(hash). Included with it is a treasure hunt where you can get rewards straight from our prize pool by finding the matching set for each of your DOOMKATs.

DOOMKATS is a special collab between leftsilverhand x (the amazing) Vector Recite. Check out my profile for the roadmap and more information.

It is an Image composition made using PureSpider's fxhash-pfp maker tool.

If you find your treasure, you need to claim it here:
https://discord.gg/BCYcxFw5SF

https://twitter.com/leftsilverhand
https://twitter.com/vector_recite

metadata.name: DOS DELIGHT: ASCII #29
metadata.description:
As a child who encountered computers in the nostalgic era of the 90s, 'Dos Delight' stands as one of my most intimate generative art projects, bridging the gap between my early childhood and vivid memories intertwined with the world of computing.

In this generative art, I aim to recreate the aesthetics of 90s computers, tapping into the nostalgia of a bygone era. The algorithm, inspired by the playfulness of childhood, generates whimsical, childlike paintings reminiscent of a time when computers were new, and learning happened through wild exploration.

Designed to emulate the unrestrained creativity of a child at play, the algorithm produces artworks with pixelated charm, vibrant colors, and blocky shapes—all rendered through the captivating lens of text aesthetics.

Press 4 or 8 to export in 4k and 8k in PNG.
Press 's' to export in screen resolution.

Murat Atimtay 2024 | @atimtay | https://www.atimtay.xyz

metadata.name: Maps of imagination #121
metadata.description:
"Maps of Imagination" is an abstract exploration of conventional cartography. 

It questions how we categorize and define the space around us. Maps can represent geographic reality, political regions, soil usage, and many other boundaries. But they are just a snapshot of one interpretation of reality.

To render at higher resolution, add &scale=2 (or 3, or 4) at the end of the url in live mode.

metadata.name: Komša #52
metadata.description:
Komšije - [ˈkɔm.ʃi.jɛ] : Neighbours (plural)
Komša -  [ˈkɔm.ʃa] : Neighbour (singular)

A play on the pronunciation of the Serbian words for neighbor and neighbours
Kom-shi-ye. Kom-sha

"Comme ci, comme ça"
 
Like this, like that.

A companion piece to 'Komšije', 'Komša' is a generative architectural napkin sketch, creating compositions based on the golden ratio.

—————

Studio Yorktown
January 2024

'Komša’ is Serbian for ‘neighbor’, and is a companion collection to the generative art series 'Komšije' created by Studio Yorktown in collaboration with Adam Berninger of Tender.

—————

Key Commands :

Press ‘S’ to save a high-resolution output of your structure.

metadata.name: Miniscapes #353
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: Timing #497
metadata.description:
Time.. 
While one thing happens one time, another happens several times.

----------------------------------------------------------------
  Keys control:
    r: toggle rotation
    i: increment rotation speed
    d: decrement rotation speed
    p: toggle show points
    s: save current size image to .png
    x + 2/4/8: save 2x/4x/8x size image to .png
    1-9 + g: save 1-9 sec animation to .gif (depends on the machine resources)

  URL parameters:
    fps=<value>: frame rate
    r=true: rotation ON
    p=false: do not show points
